headline: A Fresh Look at Willis Towers Watson’s (WTW) Valuation After Its Recent Share Price Climb
summary: Willis Towers Watson (WTW) has quietly moved higher, with the stock up about 6% over the past month and roughly 7% year to date, outpacing many insurance peers despite softer net income growth. See our latest analysis for Willis Towers Watson. That move comes after a choppy few months, with the 1 month share price return of 5.56 percent helping offset a softer 90 day share price return of negative 1.86 percent.
